It's also just a more

00:24:34.402 --> 00:24:40.917
trustworthy number and it moves
faster, so it's gotten a great

00:24:40.917 --> 00:24:46.290
deal of attention.
Why does the future market move

00:24:46.290 --> 00:24:51.240
so fast and why is it such a
popular instrument?

00:24:51.240 --> 00:24:57.487
I think the main reason is that
it is a market that--it's like a

00:24:57.487 --> 00:25:03.239
wholesale market for antiques
rather than the local antique

00:25:03.239 --> 00:25:06.076
dealer.
If you went to an antique

00:25:06.076 --> 00:25:09.987
dealer in New Haven to try to
buy some furniture for your

00:25:09.987 --> 00:25:13.339
apartment who knows what price
you would get;

00:25:13.339 --> 00:25:17.161
it would be very erratic and
you'd be dealing one-on-one with

00:25:17.161 --> 00:25:21.074
the dealer.
Well, that's what happens in

00:25:21.074 --> 00:25:25.700
the futures--in the stock market
as well.

00:25:25.700 --> 00:25:27.926
Remember, I was telling you
that a dealer has to have a

00:25:27.926 --> 00:25:30.969
bid-asked spread.
An antique dealer--they'll buy

00:25:30.969 --> 00:25:35.562
the chest of drawers at a lower
price then they'll sell it and

00:25:35.562 --> 00:25:40.156
the difference between bid and
asked is their bid-asked spread

00:25:40.156 --> 00:25:43.912
and that's their profit.
Dealers have to keep a wide

00:25:43.912 --> 00:25:47.407
bid-asked spread because they
have a lot of expenses and they

00:25:47.407 --> 00:25:50.960
have the risk of being ripped
off by more knowledgeable people

00:25:50.960 --> 00:25:54.280
who really know antiques and
will buy their best stuff and

00:25:54.280 --> 00:25:58.075
leave behind the junk.
Because they're constantly

00:25:58.075 --> 00:26:02.529
exposed to this risk antique
dealers keep wide bid-asked

00:26:02.529 --> 00:26:05.862
spreads.
It's the same with the stock

00:26:05.862 --> 00:26:08.787
market.
The people--the specialists or

00:26:08.787 --> 00:26:13.241
the dealers who trade on the
stock market with customers have

00:26:13.241 --> 00:26:16.765
the same concerns,
so they keep relatively wide

00:26:16.765 --> 00:26:19.888
bid-asked spreads.
In the futures market,

00:26:19.888 --> 00:26:23.910
there is--it's cleaner.
There's a huge volume of trade;

00:26:23.910 --> 00:26:27.439
it's very competitive;
and there's less fear about

00:26:27.439 --> 00:26:30.926
being ripped off by someone who
has special knowledge because

00:26:30.926 --> 00:26:33.890
who knows what this index is
going to do anyway.

00:26:33.890 --> 00:26:38.471
So, dealers have narrow
bid-asked spreads in the futures

00:26:38.471 --> 00:26:43.053
market and, as a result,
the futures market is where the

00:26:43.053 --> 00:26:46.000
action is.
The people who doubted that

00:26:46.000 --> 00:26:49.825
back in 1980--who doubted that
financial futures would ever

00:26:49.825 --> 00:26:53.620
take off--were really wrong.
Even though stocks are

00:26:53.620 --> 00:26:58.475
perfectly standardized--every
share is the same as every other

00:26:58.475 --> 00:27:01.500
share--we do need a futures
market,

00:27:01.500 --> 00:27:08.490
so the futures market is very
important.

