it's exactly the same as a
wheat contract.

00:33:41.039 --> 00:33:45.307
It's just a contract to deliver
1,000 barrels or receive it and

00:33:45.307 --> 00:33:49.300
if you do that you don't have to
come up with oil today.

00:33:49.300 --> 00:33:52.004
You probably never come up oil;
you just have to come up with

00:33:52.004 --> 00:33:55.269
margin today and your margin
account will reflect the change

00:33:55.269 --> 00:33:58.048
in oil prices.
This is the number you see in

00:33:58.048 --> 00:34:00.391
the newspaper.
This is when they talk about

00:34:00.391 --> 00:34:02.130
the price of oil in the
newspaper;

00:34:02.130 --> 00:34:06.986
this is it.
There's also something called

00:34:06.986 --> 00:34:11.798
Platts, which is a company
that--I guess it's a McGraw-Hill

00:34:11.798 --> 00:34:15.199
Company--that does cash prices
of oil.

00:34:15.199 --> 00:34:19.564
It's not quoted as much because
I don't think it's as reliable

00:34:19.564 --> 00:34:24.030
as this.
The problem with--you might

00:34:24.030 --> 00:34:29.030
say, this is a month in the
future.

00:34:29.030 --> 00:34:33.485
Isn't that--that's not today's
price, but that's what people

00:34:33.485 --> 00:34:37.864
are quoting as today's price
because it's the most accurate

00:34:37.864 --> 00:34:41.420
price.
Now, why is it going into

00:34:41.420 --> 00:34:45.374
backwardation?
I wanted to think about storage

00:34:45.374 --> 00:34:49.335
of oil because we were saying
that everything should be

00:34:49.335 --> 00:34:52.630
generally in contango.
Aren't they storing oil?

00:34:52.630 --> 00:34:55.928
As I said, if you drive out to
New Haven Harbor you see all

00:34:55.928 --> 00:35:00.170
these storage tanks.
Don't they have oil in them?

00:35:00.170 --> 00:35:03.480
I wanted to think a little bit
about where the oil is.

00:35:03.480 --> 00:35:08.513
Most of the oil is still in the
ground in the Persian Gulf,

00:35:08.513 --> 00:35:12.153
in Mexico, in Russia,
and all sorts of places,

00:35:12.153 --> 00:35:16.126
but we don't count that as
storage of oil because it has to

00:35:16.126 --> 00:35:20.510
be extracted and it's not just
there for sale--there's a lag.

00:35:20.510 --> 00:35:24.612
So, we have to consider oil
that's above ground and ready to

00:35:24.612 --> 00:35:27.170
go.
It is stored and it's stored

00:35:27.170 --> 00:35:30.602
here in New Haven.
In fact, the Government of the

00:35:30.602 --> 00:35:34.596
United Stated has created what
they call a "strategic petroleum

00:35:34.596 --> 00:35:37.056
reserve."
It has taken oil and it's

00:35:37.056 --> 00:35:40.495
storing it in caverns,
in caves, and this is in case

00:35:40.495 --> 00:35:44.610
of a national emergency where we
suddenly really need oil.

00:35:44.610 --> 00:35:49.104
That isn't going to affect this
market because it's being held

00:35:49.104 --> 00:35:53.230
by the Government for some war
or some terrible event.

00:35:53.230 --> 00:35:56.520
It's not on the market,
so that doesn't affect

00:35:56.520 --> 00:36:00.981
the--even though the market is
in backwardation the Government

00:36:00.981 --> 00:36:03.760
is not going to sell off this
oil,

00:36:03.760 --> 00:36:05.989
so it's not affecting the
market.

00:36:05.989 --> 00:36:09.772
The other thing that's happened
is there's a heating oil

00:36:09.772 --> 00:36:14.493
reserve;
this was created by President

00:36:14.493 --> 00:36:19.550
Clinton in the year 2000.
That is actually in two places;

00:36:19.550 --> 00:36:24.060
it's in New York and New Haven.
So, we are the storage place

00:36:24.060 --> 00:36:26.823
for heating oil.
This is not a strategic

00:36:26.823 --> 00:36:29.404
petroleum reserve,
but it's the reserve that the

00:36:29.404 --> 00:36:32.590
Government can use to stabilize
the heating oil market.

00:36:32.590 --> 00:36:36.987
They were concerned about
spikes in heating oil affecting

00:36:36.987 --> 00:36:41.150
people who are in difficult
economic circumstances.

00:36:41.150 --> 00:36:45.201
That reserve could ultimately
affect the market if the

00:36:45.201 --> 00:36:49.481
government chooses to sell it
off, but they only have two

00:36:49.481 --> 00:36:52.309
million barrels,
so it's not big.

00:36:52.309 --> 00:36:56.393
I think the first thing to
recognize about the oil market

00:36:56.393 --> 00:37:01.059
is that there isn't much storage
compared to the flow through.

00:37:01.059 --> 00:37:05.889
Basically, what we have in oil
is we have those wells all over

00:37:05.889 --> 00:37:09.619
the world pumping oil.
They put it into tankers;

00:37:09.619 --> 00:37:13.708
the tankers take it across the
ocean to various countries where

00:37:13.708 --> 00:37:17.730
it goes into temporary storage
at harbors, but it doesn't stay

00:37:17.730 --> 00:37:20.613
there long.
It keeps flowing through,

00:37:20.613 --> 00:37:25.158
then it's put on oil trucks and
it's driven to refineries and

00:37:25.158 --> 00:37:31.421
then it ends up in gas stations.
So, there's not a lot of oil in

00:37:31.421 --> 00:37:34.721
storage.
That's why the oil market is

00:37:34.721 --> 00:37:38.902
very often in backwardation,
because the price of oil

00:37:38.902 --> 00:37:42.440
reflects the temporary
scarcities of oil.

00:37:42.440 --> 00:37:45.998
If there's any shortage of oil,
if something happens,

00:37:45.998 --> 00:37:50.104
then the oil price can jump up
and everybody knows it's going

00:37:50.104 --> 00:37:55.070
to come back down;
so, you can have backwardation.

00:37:55.070 --> 00:37:58.904
Basically, you don't have
people selling off their stores

00:37:58.904 --> 00:38:03.150
when there's a backwardation
like we talked about last time.

00:38:03.150 --> 00:38:07.100
It's not like at the end of the
harvest people know--when the

00:38:07.100 --> 00:38:10.490
wheat harvest is coming in,
people know that wheat prices

00:38:10.490 --> 00:38:12.890
should go down and they sell off
their stores;

00:38:12.890 --> 00:38:17.452
it's not like that here.
The stores that we have of oil

00:38:17.452 --> 00:38:21.945
are--have a convenience yield,
so it's something that

00:38:21.945 --> 00:38:26.869
doesn't--backwardation doesn't
quickly correct itself.

00:38:26.869 --> 00:38:30.375
I think that what this means
here--this backwardation in the

00:38:30.375 --> 00:38:33.940
oil market--is that people think
that oils have spiked up,

00:38:33.940 --> 00:38:37.659
there's a temporary shortage,
and that prices are going to

00:38:37.659 --> 00:38:43.829
come down somewhat,
although not a whole lot here.

